cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the effectiveness of mobile search results, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a learning-to-rank strategy, which involves machine learning algorithms, and thus can be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG). The proposed strategy also involves interpreting user engagement metrics, which can be seen as a form of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of optimizing search results for mobile devices, which can be related to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with large-scale data from a major search engine, which can be categorized under Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
